Section : Test preparation and notes (30) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
1. Preload the latest images and OOBE.
2. Test UUIT cover 32bit and 64bit , EN and SC with Lenovo OS
3. The test need cover all keyboard devices.
4. Flash the latest BIOS.
5. Preinstall lighting control app refers to application that is pre-installed in the system and can change keyboard backlight settings(such as Legion Space,Lenovo Vantage,Legion Zone,…)
6. Testcase need test without network. If it must test with network, please activate the system before connecting network.
Note:Fin lighting include TP/ A Logo/Power button/Left D/Right D/Outlet left/Outlet Lighting,If project not support,please skip
 
Section : L1 Page Setting (90) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
Go to "settings->Personalization->Dynamic Lighting"
L1 Page: “Manage all dynamic lighting devices” page check(All devices setting page)
1. Disable/Enable Dynamic Lighting
Turn off "Use Dynamic Lighting on my devices"
Ensure keyboard backlight is not controlled by OS
Turn on "Use Dynamic Lighting on my devices"
Ensure keyboard backlight can be controlled by OS
2. Compatible apps in the foreground always control lighting
Turn off "Compatible apps in the foreground always control lighting"
Ensure keyboard backlight can work normally and this item can't impact the functionality of the lighting effect
Turn on "Compatible apps in the foreground always control lighting"
Ensure keyboard backlight can work normally and this item can't impact the functionality of the lighting effect
3. Background light control
Set "Effects" to "Rainbow" in Dynamic Lighting setting page
Ensure “Dynamic Lighting Background controller" is on the top of the list.(If it is not on the top of the list,please drag it on the top of the list)
Open preinstall lighting control app to change keyboard lighting effect
Ensure lighting effect cannot be changed
Press Fn+Space to change backlight mode
Ensure lighting effect cannot be changed
Expand "Background light control"
Drag preinstall lighting controller (eg:Legion Lighting Controller) to the top of the list
Check keyboard backlight effect
Ensure lighting effect can be changed by preinstall lighting control app or Fn+ Space
Drag "Dynamic Lighting Background controller" to the top of the list
Check keyboard backlight effect
Ensure keyboard backlight is changed to "Rainbow"
4. Brightness
Adjust brightness bar to different position
Ensure keyboard backlight brightness can be changed
5. Lighting Effects
Effects
Change keyboard backlight "Effects"(Need cover all effects)
Ensure keyboard backlight effect can be changed
Effect speed
Select lighting effect (Cover all lighting expect "Solid color" and "Gradient" )
Change Effect speed bar to different position
Ensure lighting effect speed can be changed
Direction
Select any lighting effect except "Solid color" and "Breathing"
Change the selection of "Direction"(Cover all direction selections)
Ensure lighting effect direction can be changed
Theme
Select any lighting effect except "Rainbow"
Turn on "Match my Windows accent color"
Go to "settings->Personalization->Themes" and choose a theme
Check keyboard backlight color
Ensure keyboard backlight color can match with the theme color
Turn off "Match my Windows accent color"
Check keyboard backlight color
Ensure keyboard backlight color roll back to previous lighting effect
Color
Select any lighting effect except "Rainbow"
Pick any color from the color picker
Check keyboard backlight color
Ensure lighting color can be changed
Select any color from the Custom colors
Check keyboard backlight color
Ensure lighting color can be changed
 
Section : L2 Page Setting (90) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
Go to "settings->Personalization->Dynamic Lighting"
Click Device button on the top of L1 Page and go to device Dynamic lighting page(L2 Page)
1. Disable/Enable Dynamic Lighting
Turn off "Use Dynamic Lighting on this devices"
Ensure keyboard backlight is not controlled by OS
Turn on "Use Dynamic Lighting on my devices"
Ensure keyboard backlight can be controlled by OS
2. Compatible apps in the foreground always control lighting
Turn off "Compatible apps in the foreground always control lighting"
Ensure keyboard backlight can work normally and this item can't impact the functionality of the lighting effect
Turn on "Compatible apps in the foreground always control lighting"
Ensure keyboard backlight can work normally and this item can't impact the functionality of the lighting effect
3. Background light control
Expand "Background light control"
Ensure “Dynamic Lighting Background controller" is on the top of the list.(If it is not on the top of the list,please drag it on the top of the list)
Set light color to "Rainbow" in Dynamic Lighting setting page
Open preinstall lighting control app and change keyboard backlight effect
Ensure lighting effect cannot be changed
Press Fn+Space to change backlight mode
Ensure lighting effect cannot be changed
Expand "Background light control"
Drag preinstall lighting controller (eg:Legion Lighting Controller) to the top of the list
Check keyboard backlight effect
Ensure lighting effect can be changed by preinstall lighting control app or Fn+ Space
Go back to L1 Page,expand the "Background light control"
Expand "Background light control"
1.If "preinstall lighting control app" is on the top of the list,please drag "Dynamic Lighting Background controller" to the top of list 2.If "Dynamic Lighting Background controller" is on the top of list,please click "Reset for devices"
Check keyboard backlight
Ensure the device change to rainbow effect
Go back to L2 Page,expand the "Background light control"
Ensure “Dynamic Lighting Background Controller" is at the top of the list
4. Brightness
Adjust brightness bar to different position
Ensure brightness can be changed
Go to L1 page,click "Reset for all devices" button on brightness bar
Ensure brightness can be changed follow L1 page
Go back to L2 Page,check brightness bar
Ensure L2 page brightness bar is the same as L1 page
5. Lighting effect
Change keyboard backlight "Effects"(Need cover all effects)
Ensure keyboard backlight effect can be changed
Effect Speed
Select lighting effect (Cover all lighting expect "Solid color" and "Gradient" )
Change Effect speed bar to different position
Ensure lighting effect speed can be changed
Lighting effect direction
Select any lighting effect except "Solid color" and "Breathing"
Change the selection of "Direction"(Cover all direction selections)
Ensure lighting effect direction can be changed
Theme
Select any lighting effect except "Rainbow"
Turn on "Match my Windows accent color"
Go to "settings->Personalization->Themes" and choose a theme
Check keyboard backlight color
Ensure keyboard backlight color can match with the theme color
Turn off "Match my Windows accent color"
Check keyboard backlight color
Ensure keyboard backlight color roll back to previous lighting effect
Color
Select any lighting effect except "Rainbow"
Pick any color from the color picker
Check keyboard backlight color
Ensure lighting color can be changed
Select any color from the Custom colors
Check keyboard backlight color
Ensure lighting color can be changed
Go to L1 Page,click "Reset for all devices"
Ensure keyboard backlight effect can be changed follow L1 page
Go back to L2 page
Esnure the effect is the same as L1 page
 
Section : AC/DC Switching (30) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
1)MS Dynamic Lighting mode
Drag "Dynamic Lighting Background controller" to the top of list for "Background light control"
Ensure keyboard backlight effect is controlled by MS Dynamic Lighting
Plug in/out adapter
Ensure keyboard backlight effect can’t be changed
2)App/FW mode
Turn off "Use Dynamic Lighting on my devices"
Change to Balance Mode/Performance/Custom Mode
Plug in/out adapter
Ensure keyboard backlight effect can’t be changed
Change to Quiet Mode in AC
Plug out adapter
Turn off all lighting parts Note:Allow users to turn on the lighting part again by themselves in DC quiet mode, can recover users’ last setting when returning to AC quiet mode
 
Section : Power Management (60) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
Change light effect you want in dynamic lighting setting page
Do Lockscreen/MS/S3,S4,CB,WB and then resume system,then check keyboard backlight
Ensure lighting effect can be kept after PM
